{"id": "f6cdedc37518ddf03b8653868b56020b10dc684c395f8f062278c2001050375b", "item_id": "c1812aa016:0", "text": "This pattern offers similar functionality to"}
{"id": "cdeca50a697f0260135dc19a55e479d24412d5098adce87bbd73ae6176165c1d", "item_id": "c1812aa016:9", "text": "PxrBlend"}
{"id": "50fb68245d43517e4ab4c41deced111e806f4f0e5dbd69c8694975cf7425c26b", "item_id": "c1812aa016:2", "text": ", combining with up to 8 layers, instead of only using a top and bottom layer. There is also an additional background (or base) layer."}
{"id": "5032ab2ec3726cb8e813f257ef801cd00f0f24d7b91dbaf20bf86a0cb84857ec", "item_id": "c1812aa016:4", "text": "Each layer exposes the following parameters, with [x] being a number between 0 and 7. Layers are ordered such that layer 7 is at the bottom and layer 0 is the topmost layer."}
{"id": "86acf109d1e552d9e6fd4470b55e777ed28084b57e5aba90d799351611dba978", "item_id": "c1812aa016:5", "text": "Enable [x]"}
{"id": "1ccc989c0feef3a0a4b0e4e1f1b8801094738061f356252c81daf83ab47f6558", "item_id": "c1812aa016:6", "text": "This enables the layer [x] for usage."}
{"id": "0fc38249859675301701115478c831df333a7b184a9690f90dfb42ee8e328518", "item_id": "c1812aa016:7", "text": "Operation [x]"}
{"id": "de787d343b26c1dfca70fe5f37f7f7a33d0b7de2b099fb94172d35ffb899a280", "item_id": "c1812aa016:8", "text": "The blend mode used to blend the current layer with the previous one. The behavior of the this parameter is identical to"}
{"id": "edc00d4db80ddc3e91783b63ae5fbcdfd204de983c650e9587785a40271c8f3c", "item_id": "c1812aa016:10", "text": "'s"}
{"id": "47b22d08e319f9a0807b60794c2a859df4f5f1e18fc44550ef51ba44b55c6e4a", "item_id": "c1812aa016:11", "text": "operation."}
{"id": "9bd998db95a7d5dbb9a38833f5f873145329d027e807e17e44beee2fc6cb8f8b", "item_id": "c1812aa016:12", "text": "Color [x]"}
{"id": "ef372b1d8e22e0f87b01ef451adfdd76d1447d23df9b7c83aa5c905c3afdc534", "item_id": "c1812aa016:13", "text": "The RGB input for the image layer [x]."}
{"id": "34c207676c8dce2ae4c7e8882a396a46dbee56f82c45c2a46de8178a7bacf56b", "item_id": "c1812aa016:14", "text": "Alpha [x]"}
{"id": "75b9c759cb9c3566a8d72c29adda5f049bfb128393a68832bf045244bff31b75", "item_id": "c1812aa016:15", "text": "The alpha channel of the image layer [x]. When the alpha is < 1, a black background is used under this image layer."}
{"id": "b48bc969e914f8c99f057fe30244969190bab97e709a7be85e820e792005243f", "item_id": "c1812aa016:16", "text": "Background Color"}
{"id": "fd347f3d3c3c2f2ebed59ed4aa5918b94e06204b3d459ea723719816a8af306e", "item_id": "c1812aa016:17", "text": "The RGB input for the bottom or base image."}
{"id": "f4c06e661055997e206abe727ec11dca6727c70e64476ecc0d9b606f5c0fd1ed", "item_id": "c1812aa016:18", "text": "Background Alpha"}
{"id": "108be93d1a00086ed2b27a04a0627f398b938400f71eaaf6692f57e02621a4f8", "item_id": "c1812aa016:19", "text": "The alpha channel or mask of the bottom or base image."}
{"id": "b7a76c00bd2a1e4e0c370838996637327e8c205e890f72b539a81a7abc5874e3", "item_id": "c1812aa016:21", "text": "The resulting color of all layers is clamped to 1.0"}
